{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games","anchor":"Composing-Large-Games"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them."}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s8SendableP","text":"Sendable","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A bundle lets a large game split its declarations across many types — and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"even many SPM packages — instead of cramming every "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"let room = Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into one struct. The game stores bundle instances as properties and lists"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them in its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" block; the bootstrap discovers each bundle’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"declarations by reflection, exactly as it does the game’s own."}]},{"code":["struct Attic: GameContent {","    let landing = Location { name(\"Attic Landing\") }","    let trunk = Item { name(\"steamer trunk\") }","","    var map: WorldMap { trunk.starts(in: landing) }","    var rules: Rules { trunk.before(.open) { try reply(\"It's locked.\") } }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A bundle must be stored by the game and yielded from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" as that same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instance ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var content { attic }"},{"type":"text","text":"), never freshly constructed inside the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"block. Each "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Location"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Item"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" mints a reference token at creation,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and the bootstrap matches the tokens it discovers against the tokens the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" reference; a fresh instance would carry different tokens and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fail to resolve."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent\/map","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent\/namespace","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameC